## Design Patterns

### Strategy Pattern

The refactoring implements the **Strategy Pattern** to handle different migration types.

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Open/Closed Principle: Open for extension, closed for modification
- ✅ Single Responsibility: Each processor handles one vendor
- ✅ Easy Testing: Processors can be tested independently
- ✅ Runtime Selection: Migration type determined at runtime

**Implementation:**

```java
// Strategy Interface
public interface MigrationProcessor {
    Map<String, Object> processInstitutionRecords(List<InstitutionRecord> records);
    String getMigrationType();
    default boolean supports(String migrationType) {
        return getMigrationType().equalsIgnoreCase(migrationType);
    }
}

// Concrete Strategy
@Component
public class ParchmentMigrationProcessor implements MigrationProcessor {
    @Override
    public String getMigrationType() {
        return "parchment";
    }
    
    @Override
    public Map<String, Object> processInstitutionRecords(List<InstitutionRecord> records) {
        // Parchment-specific logic
    }
}

// Factory
@Component
public class MigrationProcessorFactory {
    private final List<MigrationProcessor> processors;
    
    public MigrationProcessor getProcessor(String migrationType) {
        return processors.stream()
            .filter(p -> p.supports(migrationType))
            .findFirst()
            .orElseThrow(() -> new IllegalArgumentException(...));
    }
}
```

